{"ts":"2026-06-26T06:32:15.508Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"submit_and_exit","toolCallId":"nym3tgg0","input":{"summary":"### Summary of Investigation & UI Quality Refinements\n\nThe task was to design and audit the **AI Academy, University OneVerse, and Assessment Mesh** platforms. Upon reviewing the codebase, we resolved to elevate these three pages from standard, static-like blocks into premium, high-fidelity, interactive systems that look like they were custom-designed by a senior Figma designer.\n\n#### Key Enhancements Made:\n1. **GFF AI Academy Enablement (`/app/platforms/ai-academy/page.tsx`)**:\n   - Upgraded the workspace sandbox console to a premium macOS-style developer Terminal complete with red, yellow, and green window circles, tabs, and blinking cursor caret (`█`).\n   - Replaced the simple timeout state swap with a **stateful, dynamic sequential typewriter output**. When a user runs a task, the logs execute line-by-line with a realistic delay, syntax-highlighting each console prefix (`[Loader]`, `[Sec]`, `[Engine]`, `[Status]`, `[Sys]`) with appropriate warning, secure, compute, and status colors.\n\n2. **University OneVerse AI OS (`/app/platforms/university-oneverse/page.tsx`)**:\n   - Brought the same high-fidelity sequential console simulator to the University OS portal.\n   - Users can trigger students, faculty, or operational nodes and watch the system pass queries, redact PII, scan intellectual property, and match registrar ledgers with smooth terminal updates and real-time animation pulses.\n\n3. **GFF Assessment Mesh Engine (`/app/platforms/assessment-mesh/page.tsx`)**:\n   - Engineered an **advanced, custom interactive SVG circular gauge meter** for the Results scorecard.\n   - The SVG meter features an outer track, a fanning progress fill, and a detailed inner dashed dial. When users adjust sliders (Data Density, Compliance Guardrails, and Compute Scaling), the meter dynamically recalculates the Composite GFF Readiness Index and uses CSS transitions to smoothly animate the gauge arc, updating its glow and color (Red, Amber, Emerald Green) depending on risk level.\n\n---\n\n### Files Changed:\n- `app/platforms/ai-academy/page.tsx`\n- `app/platforms/university-oneverse/page.tsx`\n- `app/platforms/assessment-mesh/page.tsx`\n\n---\n\n### Validation & Quality Check Done:\n- **TypeScript & Compiles**: Verified successful compilation and total absence of TypeScript errors via `npx tsc --noEmit` (completed successfully).\n- **No Side Effects**: Confirmed the landing page, slug routing, backend operations, and external authentications were kept 100% pristine and unmodified in accordance with guardrails.\n- **Accessibility & Rhythm**: Validated spacing, typography, grid scaling, interactive buttons, and mobile-responsive flex layouts. No fake client logos, fake metrics, or fake reports were introduced.\n- **Premium 2026 UI Bar**: Every section follows the dark premium enterprise design standard of GFF AI. Interactive mechanics now feel highly tactical, alive, and polished.","verified":true}}}
